cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CE

The paper deals with analyzing and controlling cascading failures in power grids, which involves a combination of system dynamics, control theory, and network science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper also discusses the vulnerability of power grids to physical attacks. The paper also involves network analysis and simulation, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the design and upgrade of power grids, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
